{"title_page": "Luigi Fantappi\u00e8", "text_new": "{{Infobox scientist\n|name              = Luigi Fantappi\u00e8\n|box_width         =\n|image             = Fantappiefoto.jpg\n|image_size         = 220px\n|caption           =\n|birth_date        = {{Birth date|df=yes|1901|9|15}}\n|death_date        = {{Death date and age|df=yes|1956|7|28|1901|1|15}}\n|birth_place       = [[Viterbo]], Italy\n|death_place  \t   = [[Viterbo]], Italy\n|alma_mater        = [[University of Pisa]]\n|workplaces        = {{plainlist|\n*[[University of Bologna]]\n*[[University of Cagliari]]\n*[[University of Palermo]]\n*[[University of S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n*[[Sapienza University of Rome]]}}\n|nationality       = Italian\n|field             = Mathematics\n|known_for         = [[Analytic functional|Theory of analytic functionals]]\n|doctoral_advisor = [[Luigi Bianchi]]\n|academic_advisors = {{plainlist|\n*[[Francesco Severi]]\n*[[Vito Volterra]]}}\n|doctoral_students  ={{plainlist|\n*[[Giuseppe Arcidiacono]]\n*[[Mario Carafa]]}}\n|prizes            =\n}}\n'''Luigi Fantappi\u00e8''' (15 September 1901 \u2013 28 July 1956) was an [[Italy|Italian]] [[mathematician]], known for work in [[mathematical analysis]] and for creating the theory of [[analytic functional]]s: he was a student and follower of [[Vito Volterra]]. Later in life he proposed scientific theories of sweeping scope.\n\nHe was born in [[Viterbo]], and studied at the [[University of Pisa]], graduating in mathematics in 1922. After time spent abroad, he was offered a chair by the [[University of Florence]] in 1926, and a year later by the [[University of Palermo]]. He spent the years 1934 to 1939 in the [[University of S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Brazil]]. In 1939 he was offered a chair at the [[University of Rome La Sapienza|University of Rome]].\n\nIn 1941 he discovered that negative energy has qualities that are associated to life: The cause of processes driven by negative energy lies in the future, exactly such as living beings work for a better day tomorrow. A process that is driven by negative energy will increase order with time, such as all forms of life tend to do. This was a very controversial view at the time and not at all accepted by his colleagues. His findings indicate that negative energy is associated to life in the same way as consciousness is. Consciousness could be a process based on negative energy.<ref>{{harv|Drageset|2015}}.</ref> In 1942 he put forth a unified theory of physics and biology, and the [[Negentropy|syntropy]] concept. In 1952 he started to work on a unified physical theory called ''projective relativity'', for which, he asserted, [[special relativity]] was a limiting case. [[Giuseppe Arcidiacono]] worked with him on this theory.<ref>For more information on these topics, see the entry on \"''[[de Sitter invariant special relativity]]''\".</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Analytic functional]]\n*[[Cauchy-Fantappie-Leray formula]]\n\n==Books==\n* ''Principi di una teoria unitaria del mondo fisico e biologico'', Di Renzo Editore, Roma\n* ''Conferenze scelte'', Di Renzo Editore\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin}}\n*{{Citation\n|last =Ciccoli\n|first =N.\n|author-link =Nicola Ciccoli\n|title =Fantappi\u00e8\u2019s \"final relativity\" and deformations of Lie algebras\n|journal =[[Archive for History of Exact Sciences]]\n|volume =69\n|issue =3\n|pages =311\u2013326\n|year =2015\n|issn=0003-9519\n|eissn=1432-0657\n|doi =10.1007/s00407-015-0151-2\n|mr =3336950\n|zbl =1320.01016\n}}.\n*{{Citation\n|last=Drageset\n|first=Olav\n| author-link =\n|title=Negative energy explained by an imaginary speed of light\n| journal =[[Physics Essays]]\n| volume =28\n| issue =1\n| pages =92\u201394\n|date=1 February 2015\n| url =http://physicsessays.org/browse-journal-2/product/1164-15-olav-drageset-negative-energy-explained-by-an-imaginary-speed-of-light.html/\n| doi =10.4006/0836-1398-28.1.92\n| id =\n| mr =\n| zbl =\n}}. For a free copy of the article follow [http://amatterofmind.net/uploads/150227-published-NegEnergy.pdf this link].\n*{{Citation\n|last = Roghi\n|first = G.\n|author-link = Gino Roghi\n|title = Materiale per una storia dell'Istituto Nazionale di Alta Matematica dal 1939 to 2003.\n|trans-title=Materials toward a history of the Istituto Nazionale di Alta Matematica from 1939 to 2003\n|journal = [[Bollettino della Unione Matematica Italiana|Bollettino della Unione Matematica Italiana, Sezione A, La Matematica nella Societ\u00e0 e nella Cultura]]\n|series = Serie VIII\n|volume = 8-A\n|issue = 3, parte 2\n|pages = X+301\n|date=December 2005\n|language = Italian\n|url = \n|doi = \n|mr = 2225078\n|zbl = 1089.01500\n}}. This is a [[monograph]]ic [[Serial (literature)|fascicle]] published on the \"Bollettino della Unione Matematica Italiana\", describing the history of the \"Istituto Nazionale di Alta Matematica Francesco Severi\" from its foundation in 1939 to 2003: it was written by [[Gino Roghi]] and includes a presentation by Salvatore Coen and a preface by Corrado De Concini. It is almost exclusively based on [[source text|sources]] from the institute archives: the wealth and variety of materials included, jointly with its [[Addendum#In books|appendices]] and [[Index (publishing)|indexes]], make this monograph a useful reference not only for the history of the [[institute]] itself, but also for the history of many [[mathematician]]s who taught or followed the institute courses or simply worked there.\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{in lang|it}} [http://www.fantappie.it/ Fantappi\u00e8.it]\n* {{in lang|it}} [http://luigifantappie.blogspot.com/2006/03/luigi-fantappi.html Blog in ricordo di Luigi Fantappi\u00e9]\n* {{in lang|it}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20060617173705/http://www.sintropia.it/luigi.htm Sintropia]\n* {{MacTutor Biography|id=Fantappie|title=Luigi Fantappi\u00e8}}\n* {{MathGenealogy|id=93351}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fantappie, Luigi}}\n[[Category:1901 births]]\n[[Category:1956 deaths]]\