nica Dillon Stars in Cinemax Frightfest, \u2018Scared Topless\u2019|url=http://business.avn.com/company-news/Danica-Dillon-Stars-in-Cinemax-Frightfest-Scared-Topless-523183.html| publisher=AVN.com|accessdate=17 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Staff|title=Danica Dillon at Gold Club Centerfolds in Sacramento July 31\u2013Aug. 3|url=http://business.avn.com/company-news/Danica-Dillon-at-Gold-Club-Centerfolds-in-Sacramento-July-31-Aug-3-524425.html|publisher=AVN.com|accessdate=17 November 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nIn 2009, Dillon was working at a [[strip club]] in [[San Diego, California]], when established adult actress [[Jenna Haze]] appeared at the club as a featured dancer and told her that she should give doing porn movies a try. Within two weeks of meeting Haze, Dillon had shot her first scene.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|last=Staff|title=Profile: Danica Dillon|url=http://www.avn.com/porn-stars/Danica-Dillon-414261.html| publisher=AVN.com|accessdate=16 November 2013}}</ref> Since then, Dillon has worked for companies such as [[Hustler]], [[Naughty America]], Twistys, [[New Sensations (film studio)|New Sensations]], [[Evil Angel (studio)|Evil Angel]] and Immoral Productions.<ref name=\"auto1\"/> Since her 2009 debut, Dillon has appeared in several large-scale porn productions, such as ''[[This Ain't Avatar XXX 3D]]'' (Hustler Video), ''[[The Human Sexipede]]'' ([[Tom Byron]] Pictures), and ''Not The Three Stooges XXX''.\n\n===Appearances===\nShe was selected to be one of the presenters at the Sex Awards in [[Hollywood, California]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Staff|title=2013 Sex Awards - Stage Show|url=http://www.avn.com/galleries/2013-Sex-Awards-Stage-Show-533136/533226/|publisher=AVN.com|accessdate=16 November 2013}}</ref>\n\nDillon started [[Striptease|feature dancing]] at men's clubs in July 2013. Her first appearance was at Gold Club Centerfolds in [[Sacramento, California]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Staff|title=Danica Dillon at Gold Club Centerfolds in Sacramento July 31\u2013Aug. 3| url=http://business.avn.com/company-news/Danica-Dillon-at-Gold-Club-Centerfolds-in-Sacramento-July-31-Aug-3-524425.html| publisher=AVN.com|accessdate=17 November 2013}}</ref>\n\nDillon was featured in the May/June issue of the [[Girls of Penthouse]] in a photo set with porn actor [[Tommy Gunn (actor)|Tommy Gunn]] titled \"Danica Dillon\u2019s Cheating Ways.\"<ref name=2014FannyNom/>\n\n=== Mainstream appearances ===\nDillon made her mainstream debut in the Cinemax series ''[[Femme Fatales (TV series)|Femme Fatales]]'' in the Season 1 episode ''Angel & Demons''. Her next mainstream project was the Showtime movie ''[[Scared Topless]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Staff|title=Danica Dillon Stars in Cinemax Frightfest, \u2018Scared Topless\u2019| url=http://business.avn.com/company-news/Danica-Dillon-Stars-in-Cinemax-Frightfest-Scared-Topless-523183.html| publisher=AVN.com| accessdate=17 November 2013}}</ref> The supernatural-themed [[Thriller (genre)|thriller]] features a group of undergraduate students taking a class in \"the [[supernatural]] and the [[afterlife]].\" Her role is the daughter of a famous magician who died when she was a young girl.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n== Personal life ==\nIn early 2014, Dillon had [[breast augmentation]] surgery to increase her breast size to a 34[[Brassiere measurement#Cup sizes vary|DD]].<ref name=2014Augment>{{cite web|title=Danica Dillon Debuts New DD Look|url=http://business.avn.com/company-news/Danica-Dillon-Debuts-New-DD-Look-549980.html |website=AVN.com|publisher=Adult Video News|accessdate=29 July 2014}}</ref>\n\nDillon is married to a [[United States Navy]] [[sailor]], with whom she has a son and 2 daughters.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.timeslive.co.za/thetimes/2015/09/23/Busting-Myths-My-date-with-two-porn-stars|title= Busting Myths: My date with two porn stars|accessdate= November 2, 2015|author= Yolisa Mkele|date= September 23, 2015|publisher= [[The Times (South Africa)|The Times]]}}</ref>\n\n== Lawsuit ==\nOn 18 November 2015, it was made public that Danica was suing [[Josh Duggar]] for $500,000USD.  The lawsuit claims that Duggar physically assaulted her on two occasions after paying her for sex.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boingboing.net/2015/11/18/tea-party-exemplar-josh-duggar.html|title= Tea Party darling Josh Duggar sued by sex worker over \"violent\" physical assault|accessdate=November 20, 2015|author= Mark Frauenfelder|publisher= BoingBoing}}</ref> Dillon later dropped the lawsuit.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2016/02/05/josh-duggar-danica-dillon-case-dismissed/|title=Josh Duggar -- Porn Star Admits Lie In Sexual Assault Lawsuit ... Drops Case|date=5 February 2016|work=[[TMZ]]|accessdate=25 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Ceremony\n! Result\n! Award\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| '''2011'''\n| [[AVN Award]]\n| {{nom}}\n| Best New Starlet<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20130329112839/http://avnawards.avn.com/2011_nominations2.pdf Nominations for the 2011 AVN Awards]. Retrieved December 19, 2013.</ref>\n|-\n| [[XBIZ Award]]\n| {{nom}}\n| New Starlet of the Year<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.xbiz.com/news/128827|title= XBIZ Announces Finalist Nominees for 2011 XBIZ Awards|accessdate= 2013-12-19|author= Dan Miller|date= 2010-12-24|publisher= [[XBIZ]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''2013'''\n| [[NightMoves Award]]\n| {{won}}\n| Miss Congeniality<ref>{{cite magazine|url= http://business.avn.com/company-news/Danica-Dillon-Wins-Miss-Congeniality-NightMoves-Award-533689.html|title= Danica Dillon Wins Miss Congeniality NightMoves Award|accessdate= 2013-12-19|date= 2013-10-17|magazine= [[AVN (magazine)|AVN]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''2014'''\n| [[Fanny Award]]\n| {{nom}}\n| Most Underrated Star - \"The Who?\"<ref name=2014FannyNom>{{cite web|last1=Staff|title=Danica Dillon Featured in 'Girls of Penthouse'|url=http://business.avn.com/company-news/Danica-Dillon-Featured-in-Girls-of-Penthouse-553313.html|website=AVN.com|pub